						               													<description>Two players boardgame based on Japanese famous comic and animation series &amp;quot;Kingdom&amp;quot;. Banjo Taisen means epic battle on the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The basic setting of the game is abstract, and does not represent specific battles in the story, but the general and tactics cards give it a &amp;quot;Kingdom&amp;quot; feel.&amp;#10;Both players have the same number of Troops, Generals and Tactics cards. Depending on the stage of the rules, the size of the battlefield board and the number of pieces can be changed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each turn, player can move a single piece or a stack of pieces, play a tactical card, draw a new tactical card or place reserve piece in own camp zone.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A battle occurs when the pieces enter a square with an opponent's pieces, and each player uses their own strength to remove the opponent's pieces. The strength is based on the number of pieces, and is determined by the effects of facing, general cards and tactical cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who first eliminates the opponent's commander-in-chief or occupies the opponent's headquarters wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
